The paper discusses the use of co-occurrence matrices in information science, specifically in the context of citation analysis and web search engines. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of social network analysis and graph theory, which are relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the collection and analysis of data from the web environment, which could also place it in the Web (cs.WEB) sub-category.
